# Mobile Expo Rules

- Treat `apps/mobile` as an Expo and React Native app, not a web app.
- Do not introduce web-only APIs or DOM assumptions into mobile code.
- Preserve existing app flows for practice, check-ins, messages, and journey features.
- Reuse shared types and Supabase helpers where appropriate instead of redefining data models.
- Keep mobile interactions simple and resilient around loading, auth state, and network failures.
- Prefer patterns that fit Expo routing and React Native components already used in the app.
